comment.narrative:
The Final evaluation report is available . The recommandations are formulated as follows: 

To the Cameroonian Government: 
➢Provide efforts to mobilize counterpart funds to facilitate project implementation, once project documents are validated; 
➢Find mechanisms to monitor and fund the early warning and rapid response cells set up by the project; 
➢Establish or operate peace clubs in schools; 
➢Make operational the existing social cohesion and solidarity strategies within the ministerial departments; 
➢Revising the electoral code to clarify the notion of taking gender into account in the composition of candidate lists by establishing a minimum quota of one-third and ensuring the alternation of genders in the same proportion, in the order of candidates on the lists; 
➢Revising the general code of decentralized territorial authorities to take gender into account (minimum quota of one third) in the constitution of the list of communal and regional executives. 

To the United Nations Agencies. 
➢Mobilize resources (human, financial, material, etc.) to consolidate the achievements of this project; 
➢Take into account the Governments budgetary calendar when designing projects, to facilitate the mobilization of counterpart funds; 
➢Involve beneficiaries more closely in project design to ensure that their main concerns are taken into account in the targeted area 
➢Design a communication plan for the project and budget for it; 
➢Conduct an initial assessment of future projects. This will guide the setting of targets for key indicators, and allow for a better appreciation of the projects progress at each stage; 
➢ Ensure the assessment and effective implementation of a project monitoring and evaluation plan, as well as its effective implementation by a recruited national consultant;
